
[1]exorbitant

   EXORB'ITANT, a. [L. exorbitans.] Literally, departing from an orbit or
   usual track. Hence, deviating from the usual course; going beyond the
   appointed rules or established limits of right or propriety; hence,
   excessive; extravagant; enormous. We speak of exorbitant appetites and
   passions; exorbitant demands or claims; exorbitant taxes.

   1. Anomalous; not comprehended in a settled rule or method.

   The Jews were inured with causes exorbitant.
